        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 1:59PM CDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 159 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over La Crosse, or 12 miles west of Knox, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knox, La Crosse, Hanna, Thomaston, Toto, Lomax, English Lake, and
Brems.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
